Package org.jpws.pwslib.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ApplicationFailureException
    Exception thrown to indicate that an application context does not or can not render the IO resource that was requested from it.
    DuplicateEntryException
    Thrown to indicate an illegal attempt to insert an entry into a list which conflicts with uniqueness rules on the entry's value.
    InvalidPassphraseException
    An exception thrown to indicate that an encryption passphrase is not valid or does not pass the authentication match comparison.
    InvalidPassphrasePolicy
    An exception thrown to indicate that a passphrase policy setting is incorrect.
    LoginFailureException
    Thrown to indicate that an attempt to login into some device or network repository has failed.
    NoSuchRecordException
    Thrown to indicate that an operation on a requested record cannot be performed because such a record does not exist in the context of the executing object.
    PasswordSafeException
    Super class for all type specific exceptions of the PWS library.
    UnsupportedFileVersionException
    An exception thrown to indicate that the file is in a format that is not supported by this software.
    UserCancelException
    An IOException which signals that the user has actively cancelled an IO related program function.
    WrongFileVersionException
    Exception thrown to indicate that an incorrect file version was encountered .
